<section id="limitations">
  <div class="container">
    <details class="panel limit-box">
      <summary>What this paper does not claim</summary>
      <div class="limit-content">
        <div class="limit-item">
          <h4>Not within-person longitudinal</h4>
          <p>The study uses repeated cross-sections, not a cohort tracked over time. Phase comparisons describe population-level shifts, not individual trajectories.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <h4>Network edges are not causal directions</h4>
          <p>Edges represent conditional dependencies estimated from cross-sectional data. They do not imply that one symptom causes another.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <h4>Policy associations are exploratory</h4>
          <p>The macro-level analyses linking symptoms to policy variables are hypothesis-generating, not confirmatory. Language is deliberately correlational.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="limit-item">
          <h4>Domain mapping is interpretive</h4>
          <p>The four-domain alignment is a fixed interpretive layer chosen for cross-phase comparability, not an ontological claim about the only true structure of youth psychopathology.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

